Frequently Asked Questions
Here's where you'll find answers to some of our most frequently asked questions about working at Nordstrom.


General Questions

Question: Where can I submit a resume?Answer: To be considered for an open position, we ask that you apply to a specific job on our Careers site. We don't accept emailed resumes, however, you can attach your resume to the job application. If you are not able to complete an online application, please contact the Human Resources office at any Nordstrom location.
Question: How long does it normally take to be contacted after I apply? Answer: You'll receive an automated acknowledgment upon completing the online application process. The length of time to review all applicants depends on the position and the number of applicants. 
Question: Do you offer part-time jobs? Answer: We occasionally offer part-time jobs, depending on the specific position and business need. As a retail company, we also have seasonal hiring cycles, particularly for sales events and holiday needs. 
Question: What should I wear to my interview? Answer: We are a fashion specialty retailer and sell a wide range of styles. For the interview, business professional is appropriate. 
Question: What is the minimum age requirement for working at NordstromAnswer: : Nordstrom does not have a policy prohibiting the hiring of minors. As always, we follow applicable state and federal guidelines pertaining to hours of work limitations and prohibited duties. This may mean that for some positions, business need necessitates employing individuals who are not minors. 
Question:  I've worked for Nordstrom before. How do I reapply?  Answer: You should  create a profile then search jobs. By creating a profile, you can set job and location preferences that will automatically send job posting notifications to your inbox. To be considered for a position, all former employees will need to complete an online application.  
Question: What is Philadelphia's Fair Chance Hiring Law? Answer: The Philadelphia Fair Chance Hiring Law ensures people with criminal records are fairly considered in the recruiting process. Click here for more information. 
Question: What is E-Verify? Answer: Nordstrom participates in E-Verify for positions based in AL, AZ, GA, LA, NC, SC, TN, UT, and Hautelook Headquarters. E-Verify is a web-based system that allows an employer to determine an employee's eligibility to work in the US using information reported on an employee's Form I-9. The E-Verify system confirms eligibility with both the Social Security Administration (SSA) and Department of Homeland Security (DHS). For more information, please go to the USCIS E-Verify website. 
Question: If I refer a friend, how is their information used?Answer: Referring a job to a friend is a one-time communication. Nordstrom will not keep their email address on file unless they create an account. For more information, please review the Nordstrom Privacy Policy. 
Question: I don't have an email address — how can I apply for a position at Nordstrom? Answer: We strongly encourage you to create an email account and apply for positions online because you can create and save your profile, apply for jobs and receive email notifications when new positions that match your interests are posted. However, you can also apply for positions in person at any Nordstrom Store.
Question: If I have a dispute arise regarding my application for employment or employment while at Nordstrom, how will it be resolved? Answer: Nordstrom resolves all disputes arising out of or related to an individual's application for employment or employment with Nordstrom pursuant to the terms of Nordstrom's Dispute Resolution Agreement. A copy of Nordstrom's Dispute Resolution Agreement can be found here or can be obtained from any Nordstrom Human Resources office. 
Question: How can I request assistance or an accommodation?Answer: Applicants with disabilities who require assistance or accommodation should contact the nearest Nordstrom location, which can be identified at nordstrom.com. 

Account Questions


Question: I've forgotten my password and/or user name. What should I do?


Answer:

If you have forgotten your password, click on the 'Request a password' link on the login page. A temporary password will be sent to your email address that is on record in our system
If you have forgotten your user name, click on the 'Forgot your user name?' link on the login page. Your user name will be sent to your email address that is on record in our system
If your account is locked, please wait 15 minutes then click on 'Forgot your user name?' or 'Request a password'. The information will be sent to your email address that is on record in our system




Question: I think I have an account already. How can I confirm?Answer: If you have applied for a job and/or created a profile on the Nordstrom career site since October 21, 2009, you have an account with us. Follow the 'Create a Profile' link — it will take you to the login page. To have your user name emailed to you, simply click on 'Forgot your user name'. If you have forgotten your password, click on 'Request a password.' A temporary access code will be emailed to you. NOTE: The access code is case sensitive and will be valid for 48 hours.

Question: I am a new user and want to create a profile. Why does the system say a record already exists under the user name I selected?


Answer:If you click on New User and, while creating a user name and password, the system gives you an error message that says "a valid record already exists under this user name," it means that someone already has an account under the user name you are trying to create. We recommend creating a unique user name that includes both letters and numbers. User names must be 4-32 characters long and cannot contain spaces. 



Question: How can I upload my updated resume to my profile?Answer: You are able to upload your resume only when you create your profile. To update your resume information after you have created your profile, log into your account, click on Access My Profile on the right of the My Jobpage tab. Click to the appropriate screen in your profile to make your updates. NOTE: The maximum file size is 250KB. 
Question: I am having trouble uploading my resume. What might be the problem?Answer: Check the file size you are trying to upload. Our system can only upload files up to 250KB.
Question: How do I unsubscribe to job posting email notifications?Answer: To unsubscribe to the job posting notification emails, follow the Search Jobs link. You'll need to log in to your account, click on My Account Options at the top of the Job Search tab, scroll to the Correspondence section and click 'edit'. Then, uncheck the "send an email notification whenever a new position matching this profile becomes available" box and click 'save'. Your email preferences will now be updated. Please be aware that it may take up to 72 hours for the system to update. 
Question: Can I retake the assessment?Answer: Once you take the assessment for a specific role, it is valid for one year. You are not able to retake the same assessment within that time period. Once one year has passed, you will be automatically presented with the assessment questions when you apply.  

Question: 
                          I'm trying to login but I'm getting an access denied message. What should I do?


Answer: The access denied message could be a result of needing to clear out your Cache. Follow the directions below to clear your cache

Go to your web browser
Click on Tools from the top task bar and select internet options
Find the option Browsing history and select delete
Delete files from Cookies, History, and Temporary internet files
Click Ok
Exit out of your web browser and try to log in again











Careers Privacy Policy
Welcome to Nordstrom Careers. We respect your privacy and take the steps described below to safeguard information in our possession. We take seriously the protection and proper use of your personal information, including social security numbers (US) and social insurance numbers (Canada).


 Personal Information We Gather
When you apply for employment on our site, you will be asked to provide certain types of personal information. By “personal information” we mean names, addresses, email addresses, job experience and history, educational background, skills and interests, position(s) you are interested in, and any other information you voluntarily provide to us in a resume, cover letter, or similar. We gather this information through third-party service providers such as Taleo, in the U.S. or other jurisdictions, who may also maintain and process your information on our behalf. We may also use other service providers to assist us in the application process, including companies who assist us in providing digital interviews.
 Using the Personal Information You Provide
The initial personal information you provide and any subsequent information will be used to consider your application for employment and we will retain your application for employment and other information we collect as part of the interview process for a reasonable time period in accordance with applicable law. If employed, your personal information provided in your application will be used in Nordstrom internal systems for employment purposes. We restrict access to your information to those individuals and service providers who are involved in or provide support for the application process. We may use your telephone number, email or mailing address to contact you regarding your application or employment opportunities. We may disclose your information when you tell us to do so or to identify you, contact your or protect your rights or the rights of Nordstrom or as required by law. Nordstrom requires our third-party service providers to keep the information collected from you secure and confidential. 
 Cookies
Nordstrom Careers uses a browser feature known as a cookie, which assigns a unique identification to a computer. Cookies allow us to make our site more responsive by giving us the ability to track an applicant's clicks as they navigate through the pages of our site. You can disable cookies at any time using your browser options.
 Children's Privacy
Nordstrom will never knowingly request or collect personal information from any person under 13 years of age without prior verifiable parental consent. If we become aware that an individual is under the age of 13 and has submitted any information to Nordstrom for employment purposes without prior verifiable parental consent, we will delete his or her information from our files.
Security
 Nordstrom maintains safeguards to protect the confidentiality and security of your personal information you provide for employment purposes. To provide you with an increased level of security, online access to certain personal information will be protected with a user name or password you select. We strongly recommend that you do not disclose your password to anyone. Nordstrom will never ask you for your user name or password in any unsolicited communication. While on our website, to be sure your connection is secure you should see a closed lock in the bottom status bar (depending on your browser). If you have any questions, comments or complaints regarding our Nordstrom Careers Privacy Policy or the manner in which we or our service providers manage and use your personal information, please contact us at:

          Nordstrom Careers
          
          1700 7th Ave, Suite 1000
          
          Seattle, WA 98101
          
nordstromcareers@nordstrom.com

           For additional information regarding the manner in which we treat your personal information, please see our Nordstrom Customer Privacy Policy or Nordstrom Canada Privacy Policy.
           
          01/21/16


                    


















